commit.message: Making version 5.2
Updated reference outputs for version 5.2
Updated Xml exporters for parameterised volumes

Update support for parameterised volumes (#13)

* Updates in the previously added code:

- Added 'volumes' argument in IFactory::CreateParameterisedPlacement
  and IPlacement::ParameterisedPlacementData() and adapted implementation
  for these changes
  - this avoids relying on naming convention chosen for
    paremeterised volumes elements that may clash with existing volume
    names
- Renamed local variables so that they start with lowercase letter
- Improved debug output

* Updated test for parameterised volumes:
- Added new test Placements3 in test suites
- Split parameterisation class in two for better clarity
- Use the same names for logical and physical volumes in the added test
  (this gives better matchin in the run test output)
- Renamed local variables so that they start with lowercase letter
  and do not contain '_'

commit.message:
Added support for Geant4 parameterised volumes (#12)

* I ran into the problem, that parameterised volumes (from Geant4) were not supported in VGM. I now implemented this functionality and also the export to ROOT
* Added test environment for parameterised placements
---------

commit.message:
Root tessellated solid, fix in test suite for macOS (#9)

* Added support for Root tessellated solid:

- Added RootGM::TessellatedSolid class and updated Factory functions for its addition
- Added tessellated solid in vgm_test - Solids
  - resized it in existing implementations and resized the world volume in x axis
- Explicitly create TCanvas in TstDetectorConstruction::DrawRootGeometry()
  - required with the latest Root version (6.26/04)
- Fixed setting of tessellated solid name in Geant4GM

* Fixed test for macOS with SIP enabled, plus more:

- Added setting the DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH env variable to the executable call
- Removed trailing whitespaces

The default TGeo units (cm, s, GeV) has been changed in Root v6.22/08
